verbose_text: Accordingly, unique developmental expression patterns of different GABA A subunits are reported : alpha2 and beta3 subunit mRNA is expressed in all embryonic and adult DRG neurons, while beta2 mRNA is only present in adult ones; 37% of DRG neurons express the GABA A gamma- subunit; GABA A subunits alpha1, alpha6, beta1, gamma2L, and rho2 are absent in DRG, and the delta-subunit is only weakly expressed.
evidence: alpha2 and beta3 subunit mRNA is expressed
